data.title: Jane Wyman (Actress)
data.meta_description: Profile of actress Jane Wyman featuring biographical facts, historical events and details of Jane Wyman's personal life.
data.text:
Jane Wyman

Full Name: Sarah Jane Mayfield

Profession: Actress

Biography: The Yearling (1946), Johnny Belinda (1948), The Blue Veil (1951) and Magnificent Obsession (1954).

Born: January 5, 1917

Birthplace: Saint Joseph, Missouri, USA

Generation: Greatest Generation

Chinese Zodiac: Dragon

Star Sign: Capricorn

Died: September 10, 2007 (aged 90)

Cause of Death: Natural causes

Historical Events

"The Lost Weekend", based on Charles R. Jackson's novel, directed by Billy Wilder and starring Ray Milland and Jane Wyman premieres in Los Angeles (Academy Awards Best Picture 1946)

6th Golden Globes: Johnny Belinda, Laurence Olivier, & Jane Wyman win

21st Academy Awards: "Hamlet", Laurence Olivier & Jane Wyman win, Walter & John Huston become 1st father-and-son team to win awards

9th Golden Globes: "A Place in the Sun", Fredric March, & Jane Wyman win

Personal Life

Actor Ronald Reagan (28) weds Academy Award-winning actress Jane Wyman (23) at the Wee Kirk o' the Heather church in Glendale, California
